hondo717: checkback stayman is an alternative to “new minor forcing” played by some people. If you play it, a bid of 2@C over a 1N rebid by opener is “checkback” stayman, asking partner to show, on this hand, either 3 hearts or 4 spades. Alternatively, had responder bid spades, it would be asking opener to show 4 hearts or 3 spades. If responder has both, he should prefer the 4 card suit. If responder has neither, he should bid 2 diamonds.
